    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-03-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-03-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="40"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d40">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 184.00101/41</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minutes of the Daily Meetings of the Commissioners
                        Plenipotentiary, Saturday, March 29th, 1919</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-head" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1919-03-29">March 29, 1919</date>
                </dateline>
                <list type="participants">
                    <item>Present: <list>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. White</hi>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">General Bliss</hi>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Memorandum No. 187 was read regarding the assignment of Lt. Hubert E.
                        James to the Commission for work with Captain McIntosh in the Translation
                        Bureau. The Commissioners approved of the assignment of Lt. James for the
                        purpose indicated. <seg type="margin">Assignment of Lt. James to
                            Commission</seg>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Memorandum No. 188 was read suggesting that telegrams be sent to the
                        Department of State in reply to its inquiry as to whether any action had
                        been taken by the American Mission and by the Supreme War Council with
                        respect to a joint telegram sent by the Allied Ministers at Bucharest to
                        their Governments recommending certain action in Roumania for the purpose of
                        counter-acting Bolshevism. The Commissioners approved of the draft of the
                        telegram in question. <seg type="margin">Recommendations Counter-acting
                            Bolshevism by Allied Ministers</seg>
                    </item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
